<sect2 id="apiref.qre.logitsolve">
<title>LogitSolve</title>
<indexterm><primary>LogitSolve</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>Python usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
gList&lt;MixedSolution&gt; LogitSolve(gbtNfgSupport p_support,
                                double p_maxLam,
                                double p_stepSize,
                                bool p_fullGraph)
gList&lt;BehavSolution&gt; LogitSolve(gbtEfgSupport p_support,
                                double p_maxLam,
                                double p_stepSize,
                                bool p_fullGraph)
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>LogitSolve</function> traces
the principal branch of the logistic quantal response equilibrium
correspondence for a game, using the algorithm described in
<citation><xref linkend="Tur02"></citation>.
</para>

<para>
The behavior of the algorithm is controlled by the following
parameters:
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>maxLam</parameter>: Sets the maximum value of lambda.  The
default value is 1000.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>stepSize</parameter>: Sets the step size for the homotopy.
The default value is 0.0001.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>fullGraph</parameter>: If <literal>True</literal>, the list of behavior strategy profiles
returned contains the full sequence of profiles computed from each successive
value of lambda.  The default value is <literal>False</literal>, in which case only
the profile for the last value of lambda computed is returned.
</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

<para>
Note that the extensive form version disregards any marked
subgames.
</para>

</sect2>


